import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Load London boroughs shapefile
    london_boroughs = gpd.read_file("https://github.com/jreades/i2p/blob/master/data/src/Boroughs.gpkg?raw=true")
    
    # Merge data with shapefile
    merged_data = london_boroughs.set_index('NAME').join(data.set_index('name'))
    
    # Create a figure and axis
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, figsize=(10, 6))
    
    # Plot the choropleth map
    merged_data.plot(column='name', cmap='viridis', linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor='0.8', legend=True)
    
    # Set the title
    plt.title("What is the distribution of boroughs across London?", wrap=True)
    
    # Remove the axis
    ax.set_axis_off()
    
    # Add a colorbar
    divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
    cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.1)
    sm = plt.cm.ScalarMappable(cmap='viridis', norm=plt.Normalize(vmin=data['name'].min(), vmax=data['name'].max()))
    sm._A = []
    cbar = fig.colorbar(sm, cax=cax)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['cx'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Longitude')
    plt.axvline(data['cx'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['cx'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of boroughs based on their longitude?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='cx', ascending=False)
    max_longitude = data.iloc[0]['cx']
    max_borough = data.iloc[0]['name']
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(data['name'], data['cx'], color='c')
    ax.axhline(max_longitude, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max Longitude: {max_longitude:.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Borough')
    ax.set_ylabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_title('Which borough has the highest longitude value?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
